preview_comments.text: As a big fan of the first one i'd say that this game even though still retains some flaws from the first game is a vast improvement. I believe it was about a day or two ago that I saw a post from Deck 13 saying a patch is coming out to fix the small issues in the game such as the textures on the exosuits to show up properly. I'm 100% behind this series and the studio and if your on the fence about this game then I'd say take the leap and get it. Especially if your a fan of badass limb cutting executions, sexy looking exosuits, and a community that cares about this series. It's a definite thumbs up for me

New game! Easily the silliest game ever!
.
Tonight’s date night is an evening of drinkies, and playing Untitled Goose Game, which is quite possibly the silliest, goofiest way to spend time ever. It’s so goofy, so quirky, and so, so us!
.
I’ve not had this much silly fun since the night in Aberdeen where me and @neilwickermusic discovered Goat Simulator many moons ago, and spent the whole night cracking up at the absurdity of it. Video games are such a unique medium. You can get absolute masterpieces like God Of War, and you can get absurd simplistic goofiness like Untitled Goose Game, and they’re both super fun to spend time on! .

Age of Wonders. Planetfall (2019) - пошаговая стратегия.
⠀
Возглавьте одну из шести фракций бывшего Звездного союза и приведите её к победе. Действия игры происходят в научно-фантастической вселенной.
⠀
Геймплей игры: высаживаемся на планету, строим город, постепенно его развиваем и выполняем различные задания на карте. Победу можно одержать с помощью дипломатии или войны. Бои проходят в пошаговом режиме, схожие с XCOM 2.
⠀
Оценка 5.5/10.
⠀
Игра показалась скучной. Она сильно перегружена информацией, которую абсолютно не охота воспринимать, сюжетные диалоги не интересные, в какой-то момент перестаешь их читать. А ещё мне эта игра напомнила Civilization: Beyond Eartha, которая является 5 частью цивы с перерисованными юнитами под космическую тематику, только в Age of Wonders. Planetfall за основу взяли Age of Wonders 3.
⠀

caption.text:
Fractured factions.

Along with all the #TheLastOfUsPart2 State of Play and #OutbreakDay reveals, came the announcement that the long awaited sequel will not feature any multiplayer modes. However #NaughtyDog have teased a separate title showing "the fruits of our teams online ambition". #NaughtyDog expressed their desire to put everything they have into the single player campaign and fullfil the story they have in mind.

Although #TheLastOfUs was strongly single player focused the original title received much acclaim for its multiplayer mode "Factions". The idea of a dedicated multiplayer based upon the foundations of Factions is intriguing. From the sounds of it Factions evolved into something more during development so giving the mode its own spotlight could work out great given its own room to breathe.

Also revealed was one of the new mechanics you will encounter in game. Now there will be dogs that will be able to track your scents through shrubbery and hunt you down. Those who have been hands on with the game have said how harrowing and tense encounters are, exemplifying the darker nature of the upcoming sequel.

caption.text:
Some minecon Live 2019 thoughts: Ok so MCE and MCD we saw more footage of both, definitely cool and will get both, not really much to say on either of those. 1.15 is kinda underwhelming but that’s okay because Nether update will be coming after it with tons of new content and the honey block and bees will be great nevertheless. I’m really disappointed swamps didn’t win and I’m hoping the revamp for mountains ends up being better than what they’re advertising it as bc I would’ve definitely preferred the boat chests and mangrove tree for a new wood block and more convenient way to carry items when ocean exploring. The presentation as a whole was alright, it was watchable not really too interesting but also not completely boring. Overall though I’m happy with the constant additions of Minecraft, I seriously can’t wait till they give us more information on the nether update, and yes I am sad we didn’t get a cave update but I think with what they’re gonna be doing to the nether it will content me for the time being and HOPEFULLY next year we do see a cave update announcement

caption.text:
Werbung/ Vor 26 Jahren erschien The Legend of Zelda: Link´s Awakening zum ersten Mal – damals für den Game Boy. Jetzt kam das Spiel in neuem Gewand für die Nintendo Switch. Auch diesmal geriet Link auf einer Seereise in ein Unwetter, erleidet Schiffbruch und wird am Strand der Insel Cocolint angespült. Um nach Hause zurückzukehren, muss er herausfordernde Dungeons meistern und furchteinflössende Monster besiegen.

Ein legendäres Spiel im neuen Gewand – The Legend of Zelda: Link`s Awakening macht auf der Nintendo Switch Lite allerhand her. Spielspaß, Begeisterung und Freude im Herzen garantiert. Eine tolle Möglichkeit sich zurück in die Vergangenheit versetzten zu lassen und dem stressigen Alltag ein paar Minuten den Rücken zu kehren.

Mehr dazu gibt es heute auf dem Blog, inkl Gewinnspiel!

caption.text:
I’ve started playing RPG games since 1999 with Generation 1 and 2 in Pokémon on the Game Boy and Game Boy Colour.
2009 was, in my opinion, the year of RPG and it had me getting Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon on the Nintendo DS.
2014 given me Final Fantasy IV Remake, first game from Square-Enix, also on the Nintendo DS.
Now it’s 2019. I’m in full circle am I?
But the real question is, will Dragon Quest XI S, my second Square-Enix game, be my (near) perfect, ideal RPG?
I think me playing the demo answers my question.
